The paper deals with the problem of cell association in wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of artificial intelligence techniques such as neural networks and Q-learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the formulation of the problem as a mean-field game and the collaborative learning process may indicate a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
